{
  "name": "AWS S3 Access To Personal User Directories",
  "description": "The IT engineering team has developed an innovative idea to synchronize files from users' home directories to an S3 bucket. They intend to utilize a single bucket, **acme-user-data**, for all employees, with each user's space prefixed by their username. Your task is to create an IAM identity policy that permits users to access only their own files.\n\nAdditionally, any actions that could potentially modify the bucket itself must be strictly prohibited.\n",
  "policyType": "IDENTITY_POLICY",
  "initialPolicy": {
    "Version": "2012-10-17",
    "Statement": [
      {
        "Effect": "Allow",
        "Action": "s3:*",
        "Resource": [
          "arn:aws:s3:::acme-user-data",
          "arn:aws:s3:::acme-user-data/*"
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  "hints": [
    "Is there a way to make AWS IAM policies more dynamic?",
    "Itâ€™s important to familiarize yourself with [IAM policy variables](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/IAM/latest/UserGuide/reference_policies_variables.html)."
  ],
  "solution": "Kudos to you! Now your colleagues can sleep well knowing their file copies are safely backed up in the cloud, and none of their teammates can access them! The policy you wrote should be similar to the one outlined below:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"Version\": \"2012-10-17\",\n  \"Statement\": [\n    {\n      \"Effect\": \"Allow\",\n      \"Action\": \"s3:*\",\n      \"Resource\": [\n        \"arn:aws:s3:::acme-user-data/${aws:username}/*\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"Effect\": \"Allow\",\n      \"Action\": \"s3:ListBucket\",\n      \"Resource\": [\n        \"arn:aws:s3:::acme-user-data\"\n      ],\n      \"Condition\": {\n        \"StringLike\": {\n          \"s3:prefix\": \"${aws:username}/*\"\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nThe next challenge is already waiting for you!\n",
